  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project CLAIMED-MDM</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved collective response capacity and resiliency of disaster affected communities including duty bearers and the civil society.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide capacity building and demonstrate positive action to affected communities, including duty bearers and the civil society, on the Management of the Dead, Missing and Injured (MDM) which, is one of the most important yet overlooked aspect of the recovery phase in a post-disaster scenario. While relief efforts are understandably focused on the living, the trauma caused to surviving families over the death or loss of loved ones are largely unaddressed (especially on the aspect of legal documentation) and which oftentimes, the suffering faced by those left behind overshadow the pain and distress felt arising from damaged properties and livelihoods. Establishing the proper practices in information handling, data organisation and handling of the dead, missing and injured will help improve collective emergency response capacity and resiliency. Activities include 1) Capacity building on MDM thru Disaster Victim Identification, 2) Capacity building and actual demonstration on the Declaration of Presumptive Death for the Missing, 3) Popularization of legal research on additional benefits of the disaster affected and, 4) Assistance on the drafting of the Philippine Humanitarian Standards.</narrative>
  </description>
